Bosses of the new Battersea Power Station development have taken their plans for the iconic site on the road as they try to tempt the world's rich to take up residence in south London.

Actress Kate Beckinsale fronted a 'launch party' in Hollywood last night in the latest of a series of events aimed at attracting foreign buyers to snap up flats on the banks of the River Thames.

Glitzy public exhibitions have now been held in Paris, New York, Shanghai, Singapore, Hong Kong and Kuala Lumpur last week, followed by shows in Tokyo, Beijing, Doha and Milan this week. 

