Last last month, Sting became among the first to snap up an apartment in the redeveloped towers, adding to  his long list of properties around the world.

His wife Trudie Styler said: 'The exciting development plans for the whole site are a great solution for the regeneration of an iconic London landmark which has been in decay for the last 30 years.

'We are both very pleased to be part of this new community and really look forward to making our London home at the Battersea Power Station.'

